Use the standard library
This is how to correct_bracketing of brackets:
   Remember that depth is 0
   Remember that i is 0
   Do this brackets's length times:
      When item i in brackets is item 0 in "<", then:
         Increase depth
      But, if not:
         When item i in brackets is item 0 in ">", then:
            Decrease depth
            When depth is less than 0, then:
               The answer is 0
            End when
         End when
      End when
      Increase i
   End do
   When depth is 0, then:
      The answer is 1
   But, if not:
      The answer is 0
   End when
Now you know

>>> correct_bracketing of "<"
0
>>> correct_bracketing of "<>"
1
>>> correct_bracketing of "<<><>>"
1